data.title: Moving on: The Goodrem wife
data.meta_description: Brian McFadden might consider a version of Wherever I Lay My Hat (That’s My Home) for his next single. Following in the great Irish male tradition of letting “herself” look after the house buying
data.text:
Brian McFadden might consider a version of Wherever I Lay My Hat (That’s My Home) for his next single. Following in the great Irish male tradition of letting “herself” look after the house buying, the former Westlife singer and his fiancée, Delta Goodrem recently moved into a Hollywood Hills mansion. McFadden is said to have taken a back seat when it came to doing the deal, with the Australian singer buying the house in her name for about $3m.

On location

It looks like Jim Sheridan — or whoever lives in Martha’s Vineyard, the contemporary surfside pad the film director had built on Coliemore Road in Dalkey — is about to get a new neighbour. Dolphin Cottage, the period number next door, has just gone
